definitions.definition: Having three or more lobes or veins arising from a common point.
examples: Although palmate leaves are typical of most Western maples, a number of species have leaves without lobes.

definitions.definition: Having more than three leaflets arising from a common point, often in the form of a fan .

examples: The Palmate Newt is a common Western European amphibian.

definitions.definition: Hand -like; shaped like a hand with extended fingers

main_definition: ( chiefly botany ) Having three or more lobes or veins arising from a common point.
secondary_definitions: ( botany , of leaves ) Having more than three leaflets arising from a common point, often in the form of a fan .
( rare ) Hand -like; shaped like a hand with extended fingers
